<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2003-04-29</DATELINE><TITLE>Editors sound the SARS alarm bells</TITLE><BODY>Abstract Mediawatch: Lethal virus outbreaks may help sell newspapers but Bernard Dixon finds that the early response from journalists to the severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) has been more informed than in many previous scares with diseases resulting from other dangerous viruses.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>